        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(cli): emit commentary progress events from Claude CLI parser",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Segment assistant text at tool_use boundaries in `createCliJsonlStreamingParser`\n- Emit `onItemEvent({ kind: \"preamble\" })` for inter-tool commentary, matching the Codex backend's existing behavior\n- Plugs directly into the commentary progress system merged in #87072 -- zero channel-side changes needed\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe P2 commentary draft system (#87072) only receives events from Codex today. Claude CLI accumulates all assistant text into one blob with no phase segmentation. This PR makes Claude CLI emit the same preamble events, so Claude users get tool commentary progress too.\n\n## Files changed\n\n- `src/agents/cli-output.ts` -- `onCommentaryText` callback + dedup tracking\n- `src/agents/cli-runner/execute.ts` -- wire callback to emit preamble agent events\n- `src/agents/cli-runner/claude-live-session.ts` -- pass callback through live session path\n- `src/agents/cli-output.test.ts` -- 3 test cases\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] Existing 25 cli-output tests pass\n- [x] Commentary fires when text precedes tool_use\n- [x] No emission when no text precedes tool_use\n- [x] Deduplicates consecutive tool_use without intervening text\n",
